<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "3A">
<servcat sctnbr = "03" scnbr = "01">
<configtype typenbr = "2">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A3126003" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Rear Wheel Hub Assembly Removal and Installation
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A3126003001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle and remove rear wheel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear brake disc and rear brake caliper. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear wheel speed sensor from rear wheel hub assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4606008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear hub bolts (1), then remove rear brake disc dust cover and rear wheel hub.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B312002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.897mm" ver = "01" gw = "172" gh = "119"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove hub bolts (1) with hydraulic press, if necessary.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Removing the hub bolts will break the rotation preventing projections on the hub bolts.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Avoid removing the hub bolts unless their replacement is absolutely necessary. If the hub bolts are removed, never reuse the bolts. Replace them with new bolts.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A312002.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "54.887mm" ver = "02" gw = "173" gh = "139"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A3126003002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The rear hub bolt is pre-coated with friction stabilizer. If the bolt is reused, it may work loose.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Never reuse the rear hub bolt.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Insert new hub bolts (1) in hub holes, if removed. Rotate hub bolts slowly to assure that serrations are aligned with those made by original bolts.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A312003.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.374mm" ver = "01" gw = "171" gh = "126"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear brake disc dust cover (1) and rear wheel hub assembly and then tighten new rear hub bolts to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T3A204">
<t-part>
Rear hub bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
82
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
8.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
60.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B312003.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.063mm" ver = "01" gw = "186" gh = "123"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear wheel speed sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4606008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear brake disc and rear brake caliper. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A4306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear wheel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Confirm rear wheel alignment. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
